What you need to know:

Through the "Birdies for Good" initiative, ABSA had committed to donate Sh1,000 for every birdie made at the two tournaments while the European Tour came on board as a partner and committed to match ABSA’s donation shilling for a shillingNdung'u further thanked the European Tour for collaborating with ABSA by matching the bank’s contribution shilling for shilling, for all the birdies scored at the tournamentsAs part of the bank’s one year anniversary celebrations, ABSA invited Kenyans to submit community-based causes that need support as a result of the effects of Covid-19